title: iThor_1.1.4_iPhone_Custom_Firmware
description:
This is my first custom firmware for the iPhone. This uses 1.1.4 firmware and is activated, jailbroken and unlocked containing the 1.1.4 Baseband. This will NOT upgrade/downgrade your bootloader but WILL neuter it if necessary.

Requirements: A &#039;pwned&#039; iPhone via WinPwn or PwnageTool (Mac)

Boot Logo:

Retro rainbow Apple logo.

Standard recovery logo.

Applications

-Installer
-BSD Subsystem
-OpenSSH
-TodoList
-TermVT100
-Customize 2.0
-BossPrefs
-Taskbar notififer
-SwirlyMMS

Tweaks

-O2 UK PAYG EDGE settings applied
-Contacts icon on home screen
-Terminal backspace fix
-All applications can be upgraded/uninstalled via Installer.app
-iClarified and Customize repositories add to sources and trusted sources lists

Known Issues

-ToDoList doesn&#039;t run - type chmod -R 755 /Applications/ToDoList.app via ssh or term to fix.
